{"image_id": "CINF_2012_page_8", "image_size": [1275, 1650], "ocr": [{"text": "Cincinnati Financial Corporation – 2012 10-K - 6", "bbox": [401.3, 1600.4, 761.6, 1622.7]}, {"text": "The consolidated property casualty insurance group’s ratio of investments in common stock to statutory", "bbox": [90.0, 578.9, 1045.9, 606.5]}, {"text": "surplus was 58.1 percent at year-end 2012 compared with 54.5 percent at year-end 2011.", "bbox": [90.0, 602.9, 928.7, 630.5]}, {"text": "Cincinnati Financial Corporation’s senior debt is rated by four independent rating firms. In addition, the", "bbox": [90.0, 632.9, 1036.1, 660.5]}, {"text": "rating firms award our property casualty and life operations insurance financial strength ratings based on", "bbox": [90.0, 656.9, 1056.4, 684.5]}, {"text": "their quantitative and qualitative analyses. These ratings assess an insurer’s ability to meet financial", "bbox": [90.0, 680.9, 1014.7, 708.5]}, {"text": "obligations to policyholders and do not necessarily address all of the matters that may be important to", "bbox": [90.0, 704.9, 1029.9, 732.5]}, {"text": "shareholders. Ratings may be subject to revision or withdrawal at any time by the ratings agency, and each", "bbox": [90.0, 728.9, 1081.7, 756.5]}, {"text": "rating should be evaluated independently of any other rating.", "bbox": [90.0, 752.9, 655.2, 780.5]}, {"text": "All of our insurance subsidiaries continue to be highly rated. During 2012, three of the four ratings firms", "bbox": [89.9, 782.9, 1043.1, 810.5]}, {"text": "affirmed our insurance financial strength ratings and continued their stable outlook on the ratings. No other", "bbox": [89.9, 806.9, 1075.1, 834.6]}, {"text": "rating agency actions occurred during 2012.", "bbox": [89.9, 830.9, 501.2, 858.6]}, {"text": "As of February 25, 2013, our insurance financial strength ratings were:", "bbox": [89.9, 861.2, 745.5, 888.8]}, {"text": "On December 19, 2012, A.M. Best affirmed our financial strength ratings that it had assigned in", "bbox": [89.9, 1168.9, 970.4, 1196.6]}, {"text": "December 2008, continuing its stable outlook. A.M. Best cited our superior risk-adjusted capitalization,", "bbox": [89.9, 1193.0, 1035.9, 1220.6]}, {"text": "conservative loss reserving standards and growing use of predictive analytic modeling tools along with our", "bbox": [89.9, 1217.0, 1072.9, 1244.6]}, {"text": "historically strong operating performance. Concerns noted included geographic concentration and", "bbox": [89.9, 1241.0, 993.9, 1268.6]}, {"text": "weakened underwriting results in recent years, primarily from above-average catastrophe-related losses.", "bbox": [89.9, 1264.7, 1057.9, 1292.3]}, {"text": "A.M. Best acknowledged the strong franchise value of our insurance subsidiaries and the financial flexibility", "bbox": [89.9, 1288.7, 1081.9, 1316.4]}, {"text": "of the holding company.", "bbox": [89.9, 1312.7, 322.7, 1340.4]}, {"text": "On November 20, 2012, Fitch Ratings affirmed our insurer financial strength ratings that it had assigned in", "bbox": [89.9, 1343.0, 1071.4, 1370.6]}, {"text": "August 2009, continuing its stable outlook. Fitch cited ratings strengths including our conservative operating", "bbox": [89.9, 1367.0, 1085.4, 1394.6]}, {"text": "subsidiary capitalization supported by strong holding company cash and marketable securities position and", "bbox": [89.9, 1391.0, 1079.4, 1418.6]}, {"text": "moderate holding company leverage, and well-managed reserves. Fitch added that we have implemented", "bbox": [89.9, 1414.8, 1069.2, 1442.4]}, {"text": "predictive modeling tools that are anticipated to improve underwriting expertise and loss ratios over time.", "bbox": [89.9, 1438.8, 1057.9, 1466.4]}, {"text": "Rating concerns noted principally related to challenges from competitive market conditions and exposure to", "bbox": [89.9, 1462.8, 1083.1, 1490.4]}, {"text": "regional natural catastrophes and other weather-related losses.", "bbox": [89.9, 1486.8, 679.4, 1514.4]}, {"text": "On July 30, 2012, Standard & Poor’s Ratings Services affirmed our insurer financial ratings that it had", "bbox": [89.9, 1517.0, 1030.1, 1544.7]}, {"text": "assigned in July 2010, continuing its stable outlook. S&P said its rating was based on our strong competitive", "bbox": [89.9, 1541.1, 1090.2, 1568.7]}, {"text": "position, which is reinforced by a loyal and productive agency force and a low-cost infrastructure. S&P also", "bbox": [89.9, 1564.8, 1077.6, 1592.4]}, {"text": "(Dollars in millions)                                                              Statutory Information", "bbox": [37.1, 59.9, 578.5, 82.9]}, {"text": "2012", "bbox": [903.6, 80.9, 939.0, 104.2]}, {"text": "2011", "bbox": [1012.0, 81.6, 1047.3, 104.6]}, {"text": "Standard market property casualty insurance subsidiary", "bbox": [37.1, 124.7, 462.9, 148.1]}, {"text": "Statutory surplus", "bbox": [37.1, 146.8, 169.4, 169.8]}, {"text": "$", "bbox": [871.0, 146.1, 879.8, 169.4]}, {"text": "3,914", "bbox": [915.6, 146.5, 955.4, 169.8]}, {"text": "$", "bbox": [979.4, 146.8, 988.2, 169.8]}, {"text": "3,747", "bbox": [1024.0, 146.8, 1063.8, 169.8]}, {"text": "Risk-based capital (RBC)", "bbox": [37.1, 168.5, 230.8, 191.5]}, {"text": "3,928", "bbox": [915.6, 168.2, 955.4, 191.5]}, {"text": "3,754", "bbox": [1024.0, 168.5, 1063.8, 191.5]}, {"text": "Authorized control level risk-based capital", "bbox": [37.1, 190.3, 349.8, 213.3]}, {"text": "487", "bbox": [928.9, 189.9, 955.4, 213.3]}, {"text": "474", "bbox": [1037.3, 190.3, 1063.8, 213.3]}, {"text": "Ratio of risk-based capital to authorized control level risk-based capital", "bbox": [37.1, 212.0, 552.7, 235.0]}, {"text": "8.1", "bbox": [933.3, 211.7, 955.4, 235.0]}, {"text": "7.9", "bbox": [1041.7, 212.0, 1063.8, 235.0]}, {"text": "Written premium to surplus ratio", "bbox": [37.1, 233.7, 281.0, 256.7]}, {"text": "0.9", "bbox": [933.3, 233.4, 955.4, 256.7]}, {"text": "0.8", "bbox": [1041.7, 233.7, 1063.8, 256.7]}, {"text": "Life insurance subsidiary", "bbox": [37.1